    "body": "### Problem\n\nIt seems like diffopts defaults are not used unless they're explicitly set.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. nvim -n --clean -d old.txt new.txt +\"set diffopt?\"\n\n[old.txt](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/21955382/old.txt)\n[new.txt](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/21955388/new.txt)\n\n2. Diff looks like this at startup, note default value of diffopt is shown at bottom:\n\n<img width=\"1551\" height=\"817\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f5f38521-b0bb-49d9-8e9f-fedb75b7107e\" />\n\n3. Manually re-set the default value: `:set diffopt=internal,filler,closeoff,inline:simple,linematch:40`\n\n4. Now the diff looks much nicer:\n\n<img width=\"1551\" height=\"817\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a25de3a0-957f-4e54-9e9b-567203e48050\" />\n\nAs a workaround, setting diffopt in an init file does work.\n\nIt does not require diff mode to trigger (shows up in my normal workflow with diffview.nvim).\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ndiffopts default should be applied without having to be explicitly re-set.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.0-dev-1065+gc1fa3c7c37\n\nAlso happens 0.11.3 (without `inline:simple` option)\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a (doesn't have the same diff options)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.6\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
